-- India's overseas direct investments soars in June - RBI
-- By Himank Sharma
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 07:01AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 9 (Reuters) - Overseas direct investments by Indian corporates rose to $5.03 billion in June from $1.58 billion in the previous month, according to data released by the Reserve Bank of India on Wednesday.

The investments include equity, loans and bank guarantee issued.  Total overseas direct investments from India in June included $131.4 million in equity financing, $322.9 million in loans and $4.58 billion in guarantees, the RBI said.